    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-08-07T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-08-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="1534"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1534">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 817.48.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">American Minister to Panama</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-08-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 7, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The American Red Cross authorizes expenditure $1000 for flour, potatoes, beans,
                    rice and corn for distribution to famishing non-combatants in Nicaragua, on
                    request of our Minister there. The Commissary of the Isthmian Canal Commission
                    has been instructed by the War Department to furnish these supplies under your
                    direction. You will arrange to purchase them by draft on Secretary of State for
                    delivery to U. S. S. <hi rend="italic">Justin</hi> sailing August 9th for
                    Corinto from Balboa.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
